---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { blogPosts } from '../../../data/siteData';

export async function getStaticPaths() {
  const langs = ['en', 'es', 'ca'];
  
  return langs.flatMap((lang) => 
    blogPosts.map((post) => ({
      params: { 
        lang, 
        slug: post.slug 
      },
      props: { post }
    }))
  );
}

const { lang, slug } = Astro.params;
const { post } = Astro.props;

const translations = [
  { uri: `/en/blog/${slug}`, langCode: 'EN', langName: 'English' },
  { uri: `/es/blog/${slug}`, langCode: 'ES', langName: 'Español' },
  { uri: `/ca/blog/${slug}`, langCode: 'CA', langName: 'Català' }
];
---

<BaseLayout 
  title={post.title} 
  description={post.excerpt} 
  lang={lang as string}
  translations={translations}
>
  <article class="post-detail content-reveal">
    <header class="post-header">
      <time datetime={post.date}>{new Date(post.date).toLocaleDateString(lang, { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })}</time>
      <h1 class="text-gradient">{post.title}</h1>
      <div class="post-meta">
        <span class="author">By Carlos Matheu</span>
        <span class="divider">•</span>
        <span class="reading-time">5 min read</span>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="featured-image">
      <img src={post.image} alt="" aria-hidden="true" />
    </div>

    <div class="prose">
      <p class="lead">{post.excerpt}</p>
      <div class="main-content">
        <p>This is where the full content of the post would go, retrieved from the WordPress database via WPGraphQL. For now, this is a 2026 UI prototype demonstrating the high-performance Astro architecture.</p>
        
        <p>A key focus for this rebuild is maintaining 100/100 performance while delivering a "Spectacular" visual identity. By using Astro's static generation and zero-JS default, we ensure that content is served instantly, regardless of the user's connection or device.</p>
        
        <h2>The Architecture</h2>
        <p>Using a decoupled approach with a Headless CMS allows us to iterate on the design independently of the content. This means we can perfect the <strong>Accessibility (A11y)</strong> and <strong>User Experience (UX)</strong> before finalizing the data fetching layers.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <footer class="post-footer">
      <a href={`/${lang}/blog`} class="back-link">← Back to Blog</a>
    </footer>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .post-detail { max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: var(--space-l) 0; }
  .post-header { margin-bottom: 2.5rem; text-align: center; }
  time { color: var(--color-accent); font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 0.85rem; letter-spacing: 0.1em; }
  h1 { font-size: var(--step-5); margin: 1rem 0; line-height: 1.1; }
  .post-meta { color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 0.9rem; }
  .divider { margin: 0 0.75rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.1); }
  
  .featured-image { width: 100%; border-radius: 24px; overflow: hidden; border: var(--glass-border); margin: 3rem 0; aspect-ratio: 21/9; }
  .featured-image img { width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; }

  .prose { font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--color-text-main); }
  .lead { font-size: 1.35rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); font-weight: 500; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; line-height: 1.4; border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent); padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  .prose h2 { font-size: var(--step-2); margin-top: 3rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: var(--color-text-main); }
  .prose p { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }

  .post-footer { margin-top: 5rem; padding-top: 2.5rem; border-top: var(--glass-border); }
  .back-link { color: var(--color-accent); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; transition: var(--transition-smooth); }
  .back-link:hover { padding-left: 0.5rem; }

  .content-reveal { animation: reveal 0.8s cubic-bezier(0.23, 1, 0.32, 1) forwards; }
  @keyframes reveal { from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(20px); } to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); } }
</style>
